    {
      "id": "ba57be05_b43e39b2",
      "file_path": "test/mocks/pnfsimulator/src/test/java/org/onap/pnfsimulator/simulator/ResourceReader.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 40,
      "message": "Either make both methods static or instance accessible\n- Don't Mix static and instance access in same class. It's confusing, inconsistent especially when instance method uses public static one. \n- The readResource method is unnecessary - a whole instance is required for simple string concatenation. \n- avoid invocations between public API methods of a class - changes in one method may affect the other. If common logic is required then extract it to a private method.\n- the name 'readResourceFromBaseDir' is misleading. It does not read anything from a basedir - what actually is a basedir is not defined anywhere in this method (only the unrelated baseDirectory instance field)",
      "author": {
